{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"494b5b05-1c43-44bb-9416-aa43d6093464","content":"There are no workflow files in the current directory. This looks like an empty workspace, so let me give you general guidance on switching from `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC).\n\n## Changes needed\n\n### 1. GitHub Actions workflow\n\nReplace your current publish step with something like:\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n        with:\n          dotnet-version: '8.x'\n\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n\n      # Replace:\n      #   dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n      # With:\n      - name: Push to NuGet (trusted publishing)\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n        env:\n          NUGET_AUTH_TOKEN: ''  # Not needed; OIDC handles auth\n```\n\n**Key workflow changes:**\n- Add `permissions: id-token: write` to the job\n- Remove `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}`\n\n### 2. NuGet.org configuration\n\nOn **nuget.org**, you must register your GitHub repo as a trusted publisher:\n\n1. Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishers**\n2. Add a new **GitHub Actions** trusted publisher with:\n   - **Repository owner** – your GitHub org/user\n   - **Repository name** – your repo\n   - **Workflow filename** – e.g. `publish.yml`\n   - Optionally restrict to a specific **branch/tag/environment**\n\n### 3. Clean up\n\n- Remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo settings once verified working.\n\n### Summary\n\n| Before | After |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | OIDC token (automatic) |\n| No special permissions | `id-token: write` required |\n| Key rotation needed | No secrets to manage |\n\n> **Note:** NuGet trusted publishing is relatively new. Verify your `dotnet` SDK version supports it (`.NET SDK 8.0.400+` or later with `dotnet nuget push` OIDC support). If your SDK predates native support, use the [`nuget/setup-nuget`](https://github.com/nuget/setup-nuget) action with OIDC enabled.\n\nWould you like me to create or update a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bf733390-2223-4d13-9566-6a3fff537c0f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no workflow files in the current directory. Let me check if there are any files at all.","outputTokens":708,"requestId":"5C50:24244F:F31A25:132C184:69FFD893"},"id":"35d2b8a8-5747-4219-b2d3-9930702a7bc9","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:00:18.299Z","parentId":"c341ae57-57d1-4c6c-aa04-50adda51d0c9"}
